'''Bolaire Lathalia''' is a warlock and curator of the Lloy Wing at the [[Archanade]] museum. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Taliesin Jaffe]].

== Description ==
[[File:Bolaire Lathalia - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Bolaire Lathalia|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679660105535936}}]]

Bolaire is a gray clay mask with black lips and two dark pools where the eyes should be; behind those are reflected tiny blue lights. The mask can move, though not much.{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=94mCyd_2Q_Y|ep=Critical Role Cast Interview with Brennan Lee Mulligan Campaign 4|10:15}} 

His body is a host that the mask possesses and is clothed from head to toe, with only a long, curly red wig being visible. Bolaire typically wears a cloak to keep a low profile.

=== Personality ===
Taliesin describes Bolaire as socially between [[Percy]] and [[Molly]],{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=94mCyd_2Q_Y|ep=Critical Role Cast Interview with Brennan Lee Mulligan Campaign 4|9:57}} and as a "truthful" person.{{ep ref|ep=CRITICAL ROLE CAMPAIGN 4 INTERVIEW! MULTIPLE TABLES! NO ONE TRUSTS MATT MERCER! Brennan Lee Mulligan|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vUHrc_fXzZo&t=1s|11:12}}
{{clr|left}}

== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Bolaire claims to be one of the [[panto mask]]s, a set of sentient magical masks created by [[halfling]]s during the [[Shapers' War]] to perform a play that would kill their goddess [[Rauwyn]]. Bolaire would become dormant whenever not worn, and would be donned again many times in the next decades during wars that followed. During the [[Falconer's Rebellion]], Bolaire became dissatisfied with being used as a tool and absconded (abducting his current holder), becoming the curator of the [[Archanade]], a museum of magical artifacts.{{ep ref|ep=The Cast of Critical Role Discusses Campaign 4|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J9Mtkh1FUPA|7:22}}{{ep ref|ep=4x04|04:05:05|name=Bolaire Backstory}}

Bolaire became re-enamoured with theater after watching a play put on by [[Halandil Fang]], and befriended the bard and [[Fang family|his family]]. [[Thjazi Fang]] somehow discovered the truth of Bolaire's nature, and blackmailed him into stealing artifacts from the Archanade's archive.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|03:52:44}}

Shortly before Thjazi Fang's execution, Bolaire let [[Vaelus]] into [[Dol-Makjar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|4:19:35}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
In the moment before he died, Thjazi told his brother [[Halandil Fang]] that Bolaire had paint for him. [[Thimble]] additionally found that one of the only items left at her and Thjazi's hideout after she was attacked was a letter addressed to Bolaire. After Thjazi's execution, Bolaire arrived at Hal's home for the funeral. He made small talk with [[Tyranny]] and [[Murray]], and offered to help [[Thaisha]] with the guests. When Vaelus arrived, he pulled her aside and asked her what she was doing, and she pointed out that he had let her into the city.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} Not long after, upstairs, Thaisha opened the box she and [[Occtis]] had retrieved for Thjazi from [[Venatus]] and fell unconscious as the area swirled with mist. Bolaire was among the guests who ran upstairs to see what had happened, and when he found out, chastised Thaisha for touching magical items without checking. He and Murray took the box, which they realized was a coffin for [[Olbalad]], back to the Archanade for study, and stayed up the remainder of the night, discovering that it seemed to be extremely deep. Murray left for work and Bolaire went back to his office for further study. He found a crate of paint for Hal on his way.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} Later that day he brought the paint to Hal at the [[Hallowed Round]], having checked it and found it vaguely magical but with no clear spell effects.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

