'''Kattigan Vale''' is a [[human]] [[ranger]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Robbie Daymond]].

== Description ==
[[File:Kattigan Vale - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Kattigan Vale|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679667756060750}}]]
Kattigan is 6'4", muscular, and appears in his mid-40s. His clothes appear scavenged but high-quality, and are mostly monochrome.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|2:39:50}}

=== Personality ===
<!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.-->
{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Kattigan was a member of the [[Torn Banner]] and served during the [[Falconer's Rebellion]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|1:32}} A few days prior to Thjazi's execution, he was in [[Timmony]] on unspecified business.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|4:25:17}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Kattigan followed [[Teor]], [[Azune]], and [[Occtis]] to [[Thjazi]]'s hideout where they found [[Thimble]], and came in after they did, having been drinking since the execution. He was able to determine Thimble had likely been attacked by [[Crow Keepers]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} He joined them in going to the wake, and spoke with [[Loza Blade]] while he was there before leaving to continue to drink and eventually fall asleep in the woods. The following morning, he woke up and had [[Wulferic]] track Thimble, which led him back to [[Hal]]'s house. There, he paid his respects to Thjazi and, upon learning about the plan to save Thjazi that had failed, joined Thimble and Occtis in tracking down [[Casimir Gavendale]], a Crow Keeper and one of the two people from the plan who had not yet shown. When they arrived at the [[Guard Tower]] tavern, and Thimble asked about Casimir, they were immediately attacked.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} The fight initially went poorly for them until [[Vaelus]] entered and killed two of the Crow Keepers, and after most of them fled, Thimble, Occtis, Kattigan, and Vaelus learned that Casimir had been the traitor and sold them out, then fled to [[Gormalay]], in Timmony, pursued by [[Cyd Pridesire]]. They returned to Hal's to provide him with an updated, and Occtis and Vaelus left with [[Julien]]. After [[Teor]], [[Tyranny]], and [[Wick]] arrived at Hal's, needing to leave town, they, along with Thimble and Kattigan, decided to go follow Casimir and Cyd's trail. Kattigan warned the others that the wilderness would be dangerous.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

