== Description == [[File:Murray Mag'nesson - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Murray Mag'Nesson|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679650626408744}}]] Murray has long auburn hair and a braided chinstrap beard. She wears a big flat-brim hat and a sleeveless duster jacket. The tip of her right index finger is like an inky quill.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:46:15}} Her front three right teeth have been replaced with gemstones.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:47:53}}
=== Personality === Murray is a down to earth woman who confidentially wears her lower class background on her shoulder. She is highly intelligent, with an interest in education and teaching. She is well aware how some may take her mannerisms, and at times uses them to go underestimated. <!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.--> {{clr|left}}
== Biography == Murray works at the [[Penteveral]].{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:49:00}} She was taken in there having been a "squatter".{{ep ref|ep=4x02|3:41:02}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === Murray arrived at the funeral late, and networked with a number of the other arcanists there as well as made small talk with [[Bolaire]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} After [[Thaisha]] touched the coffin of [[Olbalad]], Murray used her ''Mage Hand'' to close it without touching it and helped Bolaire bring it to the [[Archanade]], where the two investigated it until morning. They found it was much deeper than it looked. Murray then left to go to the Penteveral, where she was stopped by a student who told her [[Ellipides Tallbarrel]] had been forced to resign. Upset, she went to his office, and learned that he had chosen to do so to prevent the [[Sundered Houses]] from prohibiting students from practicing arcane magic. They were interrupted by the arrival of [[Primus Tachonis]], who was looking for his son [[Occtis]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} During the conversation with Primus, Murray repeatedly angered him by refusing to be intimidated, to the point that he attempted to curse her and threatened to kill her. Ellipides interceded and Murray left to find [[Azune]]. The two met in Caravan Hill and discussed the Sundered Houses recent political takeovers of their respective workplaces, and decided to go to [[Hal]]'s. On the way, they learned of the fight with the [[Crow Keepers]]. At the house, they learned of [[Casimir Gavendale]]'s betrayal as well. She flirted with [[Kattigan]], and demanded an apology for [[Wick]] on behalf of his family, which he gave and she accepted.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}
