'''Occtis Tachonis''' is a [[human]] [[Hollow One]] [[wizard]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Alexander Ward]].

== Description ==
[[File:Occtis Tachonis - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Occtis Tachonis|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679664455143798}}]]
<!-- Insert character description here. -->
Occtis is a young man who is thin, with dark hair, light olive skin and bright green eyes. He wears clean but worn dark, noble clothing, with a book strapped to his leg and an array of implements around his belt.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|39:17}} He has a small fox familiar named [[Pincushion]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|2:43:19}}
=== Personality ===
<!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.-->
{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Occtis failed to demonstrate sorcerous abilities as were typical of [[House Tachonis]] and was sent by his family to the [[Penteveral]]'s boarding school to learn magic.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|52:48}}

[[Thjazi Fang]] helped Occtis when he was a child,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|44:08}} and six months prior to Thjazi's execution, Occtis and [[Thaisha]] went to [[Venatus]] to retrieve an item for him.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|21:30}} Occtis and Thaisha were also supposed to help Thjazi get away after he escaped his execution.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|2:36:16}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Occtis and Thaisha arrived at the wake together, and Occtis addressed Thjazi's body. When [[Azune]] arrived, he and Occtis decided to go find [[Thimble]], and took [[Teor]] with them as well. They found Thjazi's hideout had been ransacked and Thimble attacked. [[Kattigan]] followed them to the location and was able to determine the assailants were likely [[Crow Keepers]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} The group, including Kattigan and Thimble, returned to [[Hal]]'s home, and explained what had happened regarding the plan. Occtis comforted Thimble, and helped Azune determine why the rune on Thjazi had appeared legitimate. He had [[Pincushion]] watch [[Vaelus]] and Thimble's interaction, but both realized he was spying on them. He then stayed overnight in Thaisha's room. Upon waking up, he agreed to join Thimble and Kattigan in tracking down the Crow Keepers and [[Casimir Gavendale]]. Upon arriving at the [[Guard Tower]], after Thimble asked [[Solomon]] about Casimir, the rogues attacked.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} The fight initially went poorly until [[Vaelus]], who had followed them, arrived and killed two Crow Keepers. The group interrogated another and learned that Casimir had sold them out. They returned to Hal's house, where [[Julien]] was waiting, having been told by [[Raimond Davinos|his father]] and Lady [[Aranessa]] to find Occtis and bring him to them. Meanwhile, [[Primus Tachonis]] was asking for Occtis at the [[Penteveral]]. Occtis agreed to join Julien, and Vaelus came along to the [[Palazzo Davinos]], where Aranessa brought Occtis to a room where he could stay. She asked about the plan to save Thjazi as well as the coffin he had retrieved and the [[Stone of Nightsong]]. Occtis was somewhat evasive, but they were interrupted when his brother [[Ethrand Tachonis]] entered the room, along with six [[ghoul]]s and the Stone of Nightsong and commanded them to implant the stone in Occtis.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

