'''Thaisha Lloy''' (pronounced "TAI-shuh") is an [[orc]] [[druid]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Aabria Iyengar]].

== Description ==
[[File:Thaisha Lloy - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Thaisha Lloy|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679655416398110}}]]
Thaisha is a 6'4" orc with desaturated green skin, and long curly dark hair which is beginning to gray. Her fingers are red and black at the tips, and her eyes are black with silver and red irises. She wears fine clothes in the Lloy family colors (red for blood, and gray for the soot and scale of smiths).{{ep ref|ep=4x01|0:37:46}}

=== Personality ===
<!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.-->
{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
Thaisha was born into the noble Lloy family. Around age 19, she began a romantic relationship with [[Halandil Fang]] and they had two children together - [[Alogar]] and [[Shadia Fang]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|01:55:19}} Thaisha was inspired by Hal's art and her own family's history to become a druid of the [[Old Path]].

Prior to his arrest, [[Thjazi Fang]] sent Thaisha with [[Occtis Tachonis]] to retrieve a box from Venatus and bring it back to [[Bolaire]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|00:21:30}}

In the two weeks following Thjazi's arrest, Thaisha, Azune, Thimble, [[Casimir]], Occtis, and [[Cyd Pridesire]] formulated a plan to rescue him, involving Thimble creating a glyph of Misty Step and planting it on Thjazi. Thaisha and Occtis would be responsible for escorting Thjazi out of the city to a safe place.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|00:42:17}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Thaisha arrived at Halandil's home for Thjazi’s funeral, alongside Occtis, one of the first guests to arrive. Thaisha introduced the Fangs to Occtis and confirmed that she will be staying for the time being. She grew jasmine flowers around the entrance to the home with druidic magic, and used those flowers to welcome guests. At the wake, she mingled with other guests and recited funerary rites for Thjazi. She bonded with [[Tyranny]] while intoxicated, but sobered up to greet [[Elodie]] and [[Aranessa]]. She and [[Julien]] then exchanged heated words about his disrespect for Thjazi and about his tutelage of Thaisha's son [[Alogar]], but were interrupted by [[Vaelus]]'s arrival. Thaisha then went upstairs with Hal and opened the box she and Occtis had retrieved.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} She immediately fell unconscious, hearing the song of a nightingale, and Hal healed her. She realized that Shadia was angry at her for this. After [[Bolaire]] and [[Murray]] took the box away, Thaisha returned downstairs, and remained at the wake for the rest of the night, continuing to talk to guests. She slept in her room at the house, as did Occtis, and woke up to make breakfast with Hal and talk more with [[Thimble]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02}}

Later that day, she joined Hal in going to the [[Hallowed Round]] and had a heartfelt conversation with Shadia. Upon returning to Hal's, she learned that Julien had come to retrieve Occtis, and Wildshaped into a wolf to follow Occtis's scent. As she approached, still in this form, she and Vaelus saw each other at a distance and realized that despite being on opposite sides philosophically regarding the [[Shapers]], they would have to find commonality. Thaisha continued to run towards the [[Palazzo Davinos]].{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

