'''Vaelus''' is an [[elf]] [[paladin]] and follower of the dead goddess [[Sylandri]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Ashley Johnson]].

== Description ==
[[File:Vaelus - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Vaelus|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679662462734550}}]]

Vaelus is a tall elf with lavender skin.{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:16:33}} She is eight centuries old.<ref>{{CR|critical-recap-critical-role-c4e01-the-fall-of-thjazi-fang/|Critical Recap: Critical Role C4E01 “The Fall of Thjazi Fang”}}</ref> She wears a chainmail veil of mourning. She is heavily scarred and burned in a manner that looks arcane. She carries a censer with a very long chain.{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:07:38}}

=== Personality ===
Ashley describes Vaelus as a mysterious person,{{ep ref|ep=CRITICAL ROLE CAMPAIGN 4 INTERVIEW! MULTIPLE TABLES! NO ONE TRUSTS MATT MERCER! Brennan Lee Mulligan|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vUHrc_fXzZo&t=1s|11:07}} and someone acquainted with the history of [[Aramán]].{{ep ref|ep=The Cast of Critical Role Discusses Campaign 4|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J9Mtkh1FUPA|2:42}}
{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
Vaelus comes from the [[Mournvale]].{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:13:22}} She is a member of the [[Sisters of Sylandri]], worshippers of [[Sylandri]].{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:11:15}}
She witnessed the death of the last [[deities of Aramán|deity of Aramán]].{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:16:33}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Vaelus traveled for a few weeks from the Mournvale to [[Dol-Makjar]] to retrieve the [[Stone of Nightsong]] from [[Thjazi Fang]].{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:11:52}} [[Bolaire Lathalia]] let her into the city.{{Ep ref|ep=4x1|4:19:51}} When [[Thaisha]] touched the coffin of [[Olbalad]], she heard the song of a nightingale, and saw Vaelus as the mist cleared. [[Murray]] asked Vaelus to be kind to [[Hal]] and his family, and Vaelus promised to enact no unnecessary murder, which did not comfort [[Shadia]]. After [[Thimble]] and [[Occtis]] returned from Thjazi's hideout, Vaelus learned the stone had been stolen, and asked to speak with Thimble privately. Occtis sent [[Pincushion]] to observe the conversation, but both women noticed him. Vaelus told Thimble that she did not harm Thjazi nor was she behind his execution, and only wanted to retrieve the stone. They returned downstairs, where Hal offered Vaelus a tray of cranberry rolls but told her not to bother his family. She left and remained on the porch all night.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}}

The following day she followed Occtis, Thimble, and [[Kattigan]] to the [[Guard Tower]] where they intended to investigate Thimble's attackers, and when their combat with the [[Crow Keepers]] went poorly, she crashed through the window and killed two Crow Keepers, including [[Solomon]], at which the remainder fled. They kept one, [[Gavrey]], behind for questioning, and he told them [[Casimir Gavendale]] had paid off a large number of debts the previous day and had additionally had a deed of title to a location in [[Gormalay]], and the group realized he likely sold what had been in Thjazi's safe house, including the stone. They returned to Hal's, where [[Julien]] was waiting for Occtis. Occtis decided to go with him, and Vaelus followed. They were taken to the [[Palazzo Davinos]], where Vaelus heard a wolf's call and realized the wolf had to be let in to the garden or something terrible would happen, and made the guards open the gate. As she waited for the wolf, who was a Wildshaped Thaisha, to arrive, Julien told her he believed something bad was about to happen. Immediately after, his father, [[Raimond Davinos]], was assassinated by a member of [[House Tachonis]].{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

